shared_text:
Principal Manni
September 9 at 5:14 PM ·

Dear Families,

Just wanted to highlight what the 1st day of school will look like for our 3 groups of students.

Hybrid Group A - will be attending school in person at SFMS. Students who signed up for technology will pick it up that morning.

Hybrid Group B - students will check to see if they are able to log-in to Schoology and find their classes. Those students needing technology will pick-it up at school on Tuesday. Students will not have assignments to complete.

Distance Learning - 1st, 3rd, 5th hours classes will be synchronous (live with a teacher) & 2nd, 4th, 6th hour will be asynchronous.

Schoology training will be released very soon.

post_text:
Grade 1-5 Distance Learning Materials Disbursement

Learning materials for grades 1-5 Distance Learning students will be distributed on Thursday, September 10 from 10:00 a.m. until 6:00 p.m. at the St. Francis Area Schools District Office, 4115 Ambassador Blvd. NW, St. Francis MN 55070. Materials will also be available on Friday, September 11 from 10:00 a.m. until 2:00 p.m. also at the District Office. If you are not able to pick up materials on either date, please contact Erin Kringler at Erin.Kringler@isd15.org or 763.753.7018.

There are no additional kindergarten materials to be given out at this time.

-When arriving at the District Office pull up to the curb by the front doors of the building and show a piece of paper in your car window with your student(s) name and grade clearly written on it.
-A staff member will then get the appropriate materials and bring them to your car on a cart.
-The cart with materials will be placed beside your car.
-Please allow the staff member to step away, at least 6 feet, from the cart before you exit your car to retrieve the materials.

post_text: #SaintsPride
shared_text:
Principal Manni is with Duane Schroeder and Coral-Lyn Johnson Wyman.
August 10 at 9:13 AM ·

SFMS - Connecting the Past to the Future!

As many of you know, SFMS is going through a major remodel this summer. This picture was found during construction when the old lockers were removed. After some research, the picture is of Duane Schroeder taken in 1980 at the MN State Wrestling Tournament.

We reached out to Duane and asked if he would share his story. Here is list of his accomplishments:
-US Naval Academy Graduate
-wrestled/played Sport Judo, winning the Judo East Coast Championship
-Naval Flight Officer: E-2C Hawkeye Aircraft
-Earned a Masters in Business
-Earned a Law Degree
-Currently the Vice President (Taxes) at Medtronic, the largest medical device country in the world

Duane's message to our St. Francis family:
Success is a journey, not just showing up for game day. The effort you put in your school work, job and interests will determine where you will end up in life!

To St. Francis Area Schools Families:

As St. Francis Area Schools continues to plan for the 2020-21 school year, your input regarding instructional preferences for your student(s) is vital.

There are three instructional models that may be in effect during the 2020-21 school year. Those models are in-person learning, hybrid learning and distance learning.

Your input will help the school district allocate resources and plan for instruction the first trimester (September 8-December 3).

The deadline to complete the form is Wednesday, August 12, 4:00 p.m.

To take the survey, click: https://forms.gle/uB6Hzh18bMC2MCWf7

The Families First Coronavirus Response Act authorized the implementation of Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), a federal initiative providing students currently receiving free and reduced-price meals with a replacement food benefit to pay for groceries. This new, temporary program provides a monetary benefit to families that is intended to help supplement food costs due the closure of schools.
The Minnesota Department of Health Services (DHS) recently reported that, as of July 2, 518 children in St. Francis Area Schools are eligible, but not yet enrolled. With less than two weeks left for families to enroll before the July 31, 2020 deadline, this is a reminder to families to contact the P-EBT state hotline for more information at 651-431-4050 or 800-657-3698.

St. Francis Area Schools announces a new online enrollment process. Parents/guardians can now enroll online, saving time filling out paper forms.

Online enrollment is easy to use and is more convenient for parents/guardians. And school district staff recently trained in the new online process appreciate the increase in efficiency and accuracy of student data. Parents/guardians can call the hotline number (763-753-7157) for assistance.

*The online enrollment process is for new students only; enrollments are automatically carried forward each year for students already attending St. Francis Area Schools.

Visit www.isd15.org/enroll for more information.

post_text:
Each year, St. Francis Area Schools recognizes its retirees. This year’s in-person recognition ceremony, scheduled for May 26, had to be canceled due to the pandemic. Nevertheless, I am honored to celebrate this year’s group of 22 staff members who have (or will) retire by August 31, 2020. With combined 536 years of service, this group represents the outstanding, dedicated and skilled staff that make our school district second to none. Eight of the retirees will have served 30 or more years upon retirement! Congratulations and best wishes to each staff member upon their retirement.

—Beth Giese, Superintendent, St. Francis Area Schools

Visit https://www.isd15.org/departments/human-resources-department/retiree-recognition to view a list of retiree names.

post_text: Staff from the St. Francis High School Art Department had to come up with a new way to host the end of the trimester art show due to Distance Learning. The art show is a highlight for the department and students, and it also meets one of the visual arts standards. Staff came up with a way to create a website to showcase all of the students' artwork from the third-trimester visual arts classes. Each student had to select at least one piece of artwork for the show from their work this past trimester. SFHS students are extremely creative and here is an opportunity to view their creativity. Visit https://jenniferclose.wixsite.com/sfhsartshow to enjoy the show!

If you’d like to help us cross the finish line, you can buy a custom, engraved brick by May 22 at www.polarengraving.com/stfranciselementaryassociationofparentsandteachers

Prize drawings for brick buyers will be occurring over the next two weeks as well!

#projectplay #saintsstrong #princessunicoin

YOUTUBE.COM
Foundation 15 Video

St Francis Crier Newspaper
May 11 at 12:11 PM ·

From Foundation 15 Committee and Brent Swaggert:

For nearly 30 years, F-15 has raised money and awarded scholarships to graduating seniors in St. Francis. We created a short video celebrating some of the past recipients and some future St. Francis graduates that could one day be F-15 scholarship recipients. Big thanks to Matt Norton for helping to create the video!

Because of the great support of our community, the scholarship opportunities have grown over the years. There will be 16 recipients of F-15 scholarships later this month at the Senior Awards Celebration.

The committee is selling $10 tickets with a chance to win a total of $1,500 in prize money.
The deadline for buying tickets is Monday, May 18th and the drawing will take place on Wednesday, May 20th at 5PM via Facebook Live at the Foundation 15 Facebook page.

If you would like to participate, you can do so at this link: https://ed.co/teams/st-francis-high/foundation-15

NEW! Parenting in a Pandemic Classes:
As a parent, you may have questions about how to support and navigate these unexpected transitions as well as provide a sense of structure and routine for your child during this pandemic. Are you doing enough? Too much? Do you feel like you are carrying on three or four full time jobs all at the same time? Has your child changed emotionally? Are you worried about regression or loss or relationships?
Classes offered:
Welcome Babies
Parents of Preschoolers
Parents of K-5 Students
One Day Only with Anoka County Library

All Classes will be held thru ZOOM. Your parent educator will send you log in information once you are registered. If you have questions email melissa.denning@isd15.org

Given the difficulty in maintaining the sanitization of playground equipment and the volume/frequency of students gathering, all St. Francis Area Schools playgrounds, fields, tennis courts and track are closed to the public until further notice.

This closing comes following the executive order from Governor Walz to Stay At Home and to practice social distancing. While it may be tempting for students to use these areas on nice days, we ask families to refrain from doing so in order to reduce any spread of COVID-19.

Thank you for your cooperation.

When we’re not sheltered at home, teachers are able to bring all kinds of real world experience into their classrooms in the form of guest speakers. Melin got her degree in Theatre from University of Minnesota Duluth.

A message from St. Francis Area Schools Social Workers, Counselors and Psychologists:

To St. Francis Area Schools Families,

During this time of uncertainty, it is important that our students and families know that your mental health support staff are available for questions and support.

Support staff are available Monday-Friday, 9:00 a.m.-3:30 p.m. for preschool to grade 5 and 7:45 a.m.-2:15 p.m. for grades 6-12. Call, email or Google Meet (live video chat) -- we are here.
Visit https://www.isd15.org/district-information/covid-19-information/mental-health for contact information.

There will be lots of questions and unknowns in the coming weeks, but we will do our best to support each other.

There are so many things we want to say to our community, but often words alone can't get to the pride we feel and the thanks we'd like to offer, especially in the challenging times we've been going through and the movement from in-class to distance learning (and, yes, in this chaotic time in-between).

What has been accomplished is not the work of one person or of one group, but all of you--all of us--together.

So, in lieu of waxing poetic, we decided on this simple message:

#stfranciselementary
#saintspride
#saintsstrong
#wearetogether

post_text:
Hello St. Francis Area Schools Families, Staff and Community,

Today Minnesota Governor Walz has announced the following:

-Stay At Home order effective March 27-April 10 from Governor Walz.
-School districts will continue providing childcare for families of essential workers (Tier 1). More details to follow.
-Meals (breakfast and lunch) will be provided to anyone ages 18 and under, Monday-Friday.
-Meal distribution (curbside pick-up) at St. Francis Area Schools will be limited to once or twice a week to limit exposure. More details to follow.
-Distance Learning will begin March 30 and continue until at least April 30.
-School resumes May 5 (May 1 & May 4 are designated teacher prep days).

If you have any questions, please call the St. Francis Area Schools Hotline at 763-753-7157.

Visit www.isd15.org for updates.

post_text:
The next week or two starts a new chapter in public education. There is a huge learning curve that students and teachers will be navigating together!!

As we embark on this thing called “Distance Learning,” I am asking my Facebook friends to refrain from publicly scrutinizing their children’s teachers/schools/district for the way they are teaching or the lessons they are assigning.

Please offer grace to your child’s teacher and other school personnel. I promise that educating your children is still their #1 priority. ❤️

They are about to navigate uncharted waters with little, to no prep time. This is a crisis, not a time to be playing armchair quarterback. They love our kids and will be doing their absolute best!

🤍💻📝📌📎🖊📓📚🧮➗🖍➕

Please copy & paste if you are a teacher ... or support teachers.
And fellow educators, YOU’VE GOT THIS! I believe in you!

- Unknown author; shared post

Hello again East Bethel family! All of us here at East Bethel hope you are all doing well! We can’t express how empty our classrooms feel without the smiling faces of all our kiddos. We are wishing you all the best and hope we are finding you all happy and healthy!

Since we haven’t been able to talk to many of our kiddos we are going to try to post a couple read aloud books from some of our amazing teachers while we are away! First up is Mrs. Loso reading “The Most Magnificent Thing” sit back, relax, and enjoy!

Starting Monday, March 23: If you are in the medical or emergency field working with the COVID-19 situation, you may utilize childcare (at no cost) provided by St. Francis Area Schools.

Please fill out the Emergency Services Request Form at https://www.isd15.org/district-information/covid-19-information or call the Hotline at 763-753-7157. Childcare and/or transportation will be provided free of charge during normal school hours (9:10 am-3:40 pm) for families of emergency workers. Transportation will be offered for the children of medical or emergency providers to/from childcare.

Sign up on the Emergency Services Request Form at https://www.isd15.org/district-information/covid-19-information or call the St. Francis Area Schools Hotline at 763-753-7157. post_text: We have received many questions regarding school closure. On March 13, per the Governor's emergency directive, all Minnesota schools are closed through Friday, March 27. School districts are to use this closure period to prepare for continuity of learning. No instruction is taking place. St. Francis Area Schools Distance Learning plans are to be ready by March 30, if the Governor directs schools to remain closed. No other dates have been announced, but any new information will be posted as it is announced.
